Description: PostgreSQL extension to query and import Iceberg tables and data lake files
 pg_lake integrates Iceberg and data lake files into Postgres as a lakehouse
 system that supports transactions and fast queries on Iceberg tables.
 .
 Key features:
  * Create and modify Iceberg tables within Postgres
  * Query Parquet, CSV, JSON, and Iceberg files in object storage
  * Import data directly from object storage
  * Export query results to object storage
  * Read various geospatial formats
  * Combine different table types in SQL queries
  * Automatically infer table columns
  * High-performance query execution using DuckDB
 .
 This extension includes pg_lake_iceberg, pg_lake_table, and pg_lake_copy
 components, providing comprehensive data lake functionality for PostgreSQL.
